   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,351:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Recommendations and Next Steps
   ERROR: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,351:      pdf_renderer.py:  217: C:\Projects\documentation\architecture\mobile-application-best-practices.md:59: #10-recommendations-and-next-steps: No such file or directory
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,352:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  11 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Appendix — Glossary and References
   ERROR: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  217: C:\Projects\documentation\architecture\mobile-application-best-practices.md:60: #11-appendix--glossary-and-references: No such file or directory
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. Executive Summary
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This document provides an advisory framework for organizations evaluating secure mobile application architectures
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for Android phones/tablets and iOS devices (iPhone/iPad). It presents a decision matrix covering cross-cutting
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,393:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: concerns relevant to mobile applications that handle sensitive data, enabling informed architecture decisions based
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: on each organization
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s unique risk profile and operational context.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Key observations:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Platform selection is secondary to architecture decisions.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The choice between React Native,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Swift, and Kotlin matters less than how authentication, logging, auditing, tracing, authorization, data
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,410:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: protection, and testability are architected across the stack.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Enterprise Identity Platforms are typically a fixed constraint
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , but there is significant design
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: space in how device-level security, token flows, and credential storage are implemented around
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: them.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MFA alone may not be sufficient
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,422:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for high-assurance mobile use cases. Device attestation,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hardware-bound keys, and mutual TLS can provide meaningful defense-in-depth.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WebView shell applications present elevated security risks
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  that should be carefully evaluated
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: against the organization
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,433:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s data classification and risk tolerance.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Native platforms offer stronger security primitives
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  than cross-platform frameworks, but React
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Native can be a viable option when paired with proper native module bridges for security-critical
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: operations.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,445:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Security Incident Event (SIE) response capabilities
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  should be a primary consideration when
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: selecting an architecture, as the ability to rapidly detect, contain, and remediate incidents varies
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: significantly across platform choices.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. Scope and Purpose
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This guide serves as an 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: advisory decision framework
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — not a prescriptive mandate, certification, or approval. It is
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: intended to:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Enumerate 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all cross-cutting concerns
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  that should be addressed before writing the first line of code
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Provide a 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,477:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: pros and cons analysis
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,478:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for each platform choice against each concern
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Present the 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,483:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: complete authentication and identity landscape
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  available within GC constraints
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Offer a 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,485:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: decision tree
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  that Federal departments can follow based on their specific risk profile, user
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: base, and operational requirements
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: In Scope:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,492:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Android (phones + tablets), iOS (iPhone + iPad), authentication, authorization, logging, auditing, tracing,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: performance, testability, scalability, accessibility, localization, data sovereignty, security architecture.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Out of Scope:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Backend API design, cloud infrastructure, MDM/EMM policy (referenced but not detailed), desktop
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: or web applications.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. Platform Selection — Decision Framework
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.1 Native iOS (Swift / SwiftUI)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Pros:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,513:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Area | Detail |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,515:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Security
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Direct access to the Secure Enclave, Keychain Services, CryptoKit, and
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: App Attest API. No JavaScript bridge to intercept. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Performance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Compiled to native ARM binaries; no runtime
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: interpretation layer. Optimal for computationally intensive cryptographic operations. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hardware Integration
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Full access to biometrics (Face ID, Touch ID), NFC, Bluetooth, and device sensors without third-party wrappers. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OS Updates
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Typically same-day support for new iOS features, security patches, and API changes. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: App Store
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compliance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Apple
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s review process favors native apps; fewer rejection risks related to WebView or dynamic code
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: loading. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,537:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Testability
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | XCTest, XCUITest provide deep integration testing capabilities with Xcode Instruments for
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,540:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: profiling. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Code Signing
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Tightly controlled by Apple — code integrity verification is built into the platform. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cons:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Area | Detail |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,545:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: iOS-only
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,549:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | No code reuse for Android. Requires a completely separate Android
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: codebase. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Talent Pool
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Smaller pool of Swift developers compared to JavaScript/TypeScript (React Native). |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Development Cost
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,562:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Maintaining two separate native codebases (iOS + Android) increases development and
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: maintenance cost by an estimated 40–70%. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,564:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Release Cadence
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | App Store review process can introduce delays (1–7
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,566:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: days). |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.2 Native Android (Kotlin / Jetpack Compose)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Pros:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Area | Detail |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,569:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Security
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Direct access to Android Keystore (hardware-backed on most modern
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: devices), SafetyNet/Play Integrity API, StrongBox. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,577:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Performance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | ART-compiled; near-native performance for
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all operations. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Device Diversity
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Supports the wide range of GC-issued Android devices (Samsung
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Knox-enrolled, Google Pixel, etc.). |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,585:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MDM Integration
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Deep integration with Android Enterprise for managed
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: device profiles, work profiles, and COPE/BYOD scenarios. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,591:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Testability
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Espresso, UI Automator, and
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Robolectric provide comprehensive testing at unit, integration, and UI levels. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,597:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,600:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Open Ecosystem
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Greater
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: flexibility in distribution (Play Store, enterprise sideloading, managed Google Play). |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,606:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cons:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,607:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Area | Detail |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fragmentation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Wide variance in hardware security module quality across device
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: manufacturers. Not all Android devices have hardware-backed keystores. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Android-only
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | No code reuse for iOS. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Security Inconsistency
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | HSM-level security varies by OEM; Samsung Knox provides stronger guarantees than
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: generic AOSP devices. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Update Lag
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Android OS updates are manufacturer-dependent; security patch adoption is
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: inconsistent. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.3 Cross-Platform — React Native
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,632:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Pros:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Area | Detail |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Code Reuse
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 70–90% shared codebase across iOS and Android, reducing development
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and maintenance cost. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Talent Availability
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Large pool of JavaScript/TypeScript developers. Easier to staff. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Development Speed
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Hot-reloading, single codebase, and a mature ecosystem accelerate development. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Ecosystem
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Rich library ecosystem (navigation, state management, etc.). Expo framework simplifies build tooling. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Local Execution
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | All HTML, JavaScript, and application logic runs locally on device — not fetched from a remote
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: server. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cons:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,653:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Area | Detail |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,654:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,655:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Security Surface
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | JavaScript bridge introduces an additional attack surface. Native
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,664:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: module calls cross a serialization boundary that can be intercepted on rooted/jailbroken devices. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: HSM Access
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,669:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,670:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No direct access to Secure Enclave or Android Keystore from JavaScript — requires native module bridges (e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,672:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: react-native-keychain
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , custom native modules). |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,674:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Performance Overhead
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | JS ↔ Native bridge imposes
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: latency for security-critical operations. The new architecture (JSI/TurboModules) reduces but does not eliminate
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: this. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,692:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,693:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OS Feature Lag
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | New OS security features (e.g., Apple
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,694:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,695:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s App Attest, Android
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,696:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,697:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Key Attestation) require
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,698:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: native module updates, introducing delay. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,700:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,701:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Supply-Chain Risk
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,703:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Heavy dependency on npm packages; each
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: dependency is a potential supply-chain attack vector. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,705:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Code Obfuscation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | JavaScript bundles are harder to
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: obfuscate effectively compared to compiled Swift/Kotlin binaries. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,710:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Dynamic Code Risk
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,712:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Although React Native
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: runs locally, the use of 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,713:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: eval()
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , dynamic imports, or over-the-air (OTA) update mechanisms (e.g., CodePush) can
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,718:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: introduce runtime code injection risks if not locked down. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,719:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.4 Hybrid / WebView Shell Applications
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ⚠️ Organizations should carefully evaluate the security trade-offs of this pattern before
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: adoption, particularly for applications handling sensitive data.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,785:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: shell app
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is a native application wrapper that embeds a full-screen 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WKWebView
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (iOS) or 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WebView
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Android)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: to render a remotely-hosted web application.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Pros:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Area | Detail |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Development Cost
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Minimal mobile-specific development; reuses an existing web
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: application. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Update Speed
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Web content can be updated server-side without app store releases. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cons — Security Risks:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Risk | Detail |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|--------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No Code Integrity
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Content is fetched remotely at runtime. There is no compile-time
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: integrity verification. A compromised CDN or MITM attack can inject arbitrary code. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Token Exposure
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Tokens
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stored in 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: localStorage
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sessionStorage
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , or cookies within the WebView are accessible to injected scripts
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: via XSS. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No HSM Access
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | WebView JavaScript has no access to Secure Enclave, Keychain, or Android
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Keystore. Credentials cannot be hardware-protected. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cookie/Session Hijacking
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | WebView cookie stores can be
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: extracted on rooted/jailbroken devices. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: JavaScript Bridge Exploits
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | If native ↔ WebView bridges are exposed (e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: addJavascriptInterface
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  on Android), any script running in the WebView can invoke native APIs. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TLS
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Pinning Bypass
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | WebView TLS behavior is controlled by the system; implementing certificate pinning is difficult
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: or impossible. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No App Attest / Play Integrity
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Shell apps cannot meaningfully participate in device attestation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: because the 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: application
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is a web page, not a verifiable binary. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Data Leakage
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | WebView caches (HTTP cache,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DOM storage) persist on disk and can be forensically extracted. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Content Security Policy Limitations
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | CSP
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: headers apply to the web content but do not protect the native bridge layer. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Bottom Line:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A WebView shell is functionally equivalent to running a browser bookmark. It provides no additional
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: security controls beyond what a standard mobile browser offers, while creating a false sense of security by
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: appearing as a 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: native app.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Organizations handling classified or sensitive data should 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: carefully assess whether
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: this pattern meets their security requirements
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  given these inherent limitations.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.5 Platform Comparison Matrix
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Concern | Native iOS (Swift) | Native Android (Kotlin) | React Native | WebView Shell |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---------|-------------------|------------------------|--------------|---------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | HSM / Secure Enclave Access | ✅ Direct | ✅ Direct
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:29,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (device-dependent) | ⚠️ Via native bridge | ❌ None |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,001:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Code Integrity | ✅ Compiled + signed | ✅ Compiled + signed | ⚠️ JS bundle
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can be extracted | ❌ Remote code |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,005:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,006:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | App Attestation | ✅ App Attest API | ✅ Play Integrity API | ⚠️ Requires native module | ❌ Not
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: possible |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,007:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Certificate Pinning | ✅ Native | ✅ Native | ⚠️ Via native module | ❌ Extremely limited |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Biometric Auth | ✅
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: LocalAuthentication | ✅ BiometricPrompt | ⚠️ Via bridge | ❌ Not available |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Performance | ✅ Excellent | ✅ Excellent | ⚠️ Good
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (bridge overhead) | ❌ Poor (web rendering) |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Code Reuse | ❌ iOS only | ❌ Android only | ✅ 70-90% shared | ✅ Web reuse |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,026:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Development Cost | ❌ High (per platform) | ❌ High (per platform) | ✅ Lower | ✅ Lowest |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | WCAG / Accessibility | ✅ UIAccessibility
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | ✅ AccessibilityService | ⚠️ Partial (varies by component) | ⚠️ Web accessibility |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | OTA Security Updates | ❌ App Store
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: required | ❌ Play Store required | ⚠️ CodePush (risky) | ✅ Server-side |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Supply-Chain Risk | ✅ Low (CocoaPods/SPM) | ✅ Low
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Gradle) | ❌ High (npm) | ❌ High (CDN + npm) |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,045:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4. Authentication and Identity Architecture
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.1 Enterprise Identity Platform — Organizational Constraint
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Most enterprise environments authenticate against a centralized 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Identity Provider (IdP)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . In the Government of
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Canada context, this is the GC Sign-In / Trusted Digital Identity framework. This is typically a non-negotiable
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: requirement driven by organizational policy, including:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Treasury Board Policy on Service and Digital
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,061:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — references use of GC enterprise identity services
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,063:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ITPIN 2018-01
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — direction on trusted digital identity
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CCCS guidance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — alignment with Canadian Centre for Cyber Security recommendations
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Note:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The following architectural considerations apply broadly to any enterprise IdP integration.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Organizations should verify these constraints against their own identity governance policies.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What this means architecturally:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,078:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The mobile app is typically a 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,079:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Relying Party (RP)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,080:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — it does not manage credentials directly
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,081:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Authentication flows should use 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,082:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: standard protocols
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,083:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (OAuth 2.0/2.1, OpenID Connect) against the
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: enterprise IdP
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,085:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The app 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: should not
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  implement its own username/password store or custom credential scheme
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,087:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: All session management is typically token-based; the IdP issues tokens, the app validates and stores
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: them securely
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Degrees of Freedom:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  While the IdP is fixed, there is significant design space in:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,091:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,092:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How tokens are stored on-device (software vs. hardware-backed)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,093:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,094:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How device identity is coupled with user identity
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,095:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,096:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How token renewal minimizes login prompts
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,098:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,100:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How additional attestation layers complement the IdP assertion
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.2 OAuth 2.1 and Device-Bound Token Flows
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OAuth 2.1 (consolidation of OAuth 2.0 best practices, RFC 9700) is the recommended authorization framework.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Key flows for mobile:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.2.1 Authorization Code Flow with PKCE (Mandatory)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ┌──────────┐                                    ┌──────────────┐
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  Mobile   │──(1) Auth Request + code_challenge──▶│   GC IdP      │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  App      │                                    │  (Auth Server)│
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │           │◀──(2) Authorization Code───────────│               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │           │──(3) Token Request + code_verifier──▶│               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │           │◀──(4) Access Token + Refresh Token──│               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,144:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: └──────────┘                                    └──────────────┘
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,145:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PKCE is strongly recommended
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (and required under OAuth 2.1) — mitigates authorization code
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: interception
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The implicit flow is 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: not recommended
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  under OAuth 2.1
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Client secrets 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: should not
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  be embedded in mobile applications
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.2.2 Device-Bound Token Enhancement (DPoP — Demonstrating Proof-of-Possession)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Standard bearer tokens are vulnerable if extracted from device storage. 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DPoP (RFC 9449)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  binds tokens to a
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: device-specific cryptographic key:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ┌──────────┐                                     ┌──────────────┐
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  Mobile   │──(1) Generate key pair in HSM──────▶│ Secure Enclave│
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  App      │◀──(1a) Public key reference─────────│ / Keystore    │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │           │                                     └──────────────┘
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,161:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │           │──(2) Token Request + DPoP Proof──────▶┌──────────────┐
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │           │◀──(3) DPoP-bound Access Token────────│   GC IdP      │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │           │                                      └──────────────┘
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │           │──(4) API Request + DPoP Proof────────▶┌──────────────┐
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,165:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │           │   (signed by device HSM key)          │  Resource     │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │           │◀──(5) Protected Resource─────────────│  Server       │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: └──────────┘                                      └──────────────┘
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: How this enhances security:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Even if tokens are stolen from device storage, they are 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cryptographically useless
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  without access to
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the HSM-bound private key
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Each API request includes a 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: proof-of-possession
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  signed by the device
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s hardware-protected key
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The resource server validates both the token 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  the proof, ensuring the presenting device is the
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: intended recipient
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Token + Device Information Flow:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                      DPoP Token Payload                         │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  Standard Claims:                                               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    iss: https://gc-idp.canada.ca                                │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    sub: <user-id>                                               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    aud: <api-resource-identifier>                               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    exp: <short-lived, e.g. 5 minutes>                           │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    iat: <issued-at>                                             │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                                                                 │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  DPoP Proof (JWT Header):                                       │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    typ: dpop+jwt                                                │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,196:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    alg: ES256 (ECDSA with P-256)                                │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    jwk: <device public key from HSM>                            │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,198:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                                                                 │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  DPoP Proof (JWT Payload):                                      │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    htm: POST                                                    │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    htu: https://api.service.canada.ca/resource                  │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,202:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    iat: <timestamp>                                             │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    jti: <unique-per-request nonce>                               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                                                                 │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  Device Context (Custom Claims for Zero-Trust):                 │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    cnf.jkt: <JWK thumbprint of device key>                      │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    device_integrity: <Play Integrity / App Attest token>        │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │    device_id: <hardware-derived identifier>                     │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,209:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.2.3 Refresh Token Rotation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,211:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Refresh tokens 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: should
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  be rotated on every use (as recommended by OAuth 2.1)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Previous refresh tokens are invalidated immediately upon rotation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Refresh tokens should be stored in HSM-backed storage (Keychain with 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: kSecAttrAccessibleWhenUnlockedThisDeviceOnly
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  on iOS,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: EncryptedSharedPreferences backed by Android Keystore)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Refresh token lifetime should be bounded (e.g., 24–48 hours) with re-authentication required beyond
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: that window
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.3 OpenID Connect (OIDC) and Claims-Based Identity
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OpenID Connect is the identity layer built on top of OAuth 2.1. It provides:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ID Token
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,229:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — a signed JWT asserting user identity, authentication time, authentication method, and
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: assurance level
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,230:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,231:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: UserInfo Endpoint
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — additional claims about the user
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,234:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Standard Claims
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,235:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sub
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,236:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: email
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,237:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: name
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,238:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: locale
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: , 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amr
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (authentication methods reference)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Critical for GC Mobile Apps:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | OIDC Feature | GC Application |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,242:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,243:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------------|----------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: acr
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Authentication Context Class Reference) |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Maps to GC assurance levels (e.g., LOA2, LOA3). Mobile apps should 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: request and validate
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  the appropriate
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: assurance level. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: amr
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Authentication Methods Reference) | Indicates how the user authenticated (e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ["pwd",
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "otp", "hwk"]
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ). The app should verify that hardware-key-based authentication was used when required. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: auth_time
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Timestamp of authentication. The app should enforce maximum session age policies. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: at_hash
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Access token hash — validates that the access token was issued alongside the ID token. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,271:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Claims Request Parameter |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Request specific claims (e.g., department, clearance level, role) for fine-grained authorization. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OIDC + Device Binding Flow:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. App initiates OIDC flow with scope: openid profile gc-assurance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. GC IdP authenticates user (password + MFA + optional device
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,276:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: attestation)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,277:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. GC IdP returns:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,278:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    - ID Token (user identity + assurance level + auth methods)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,279:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    - Access Token (API authorization, DPoP-bound)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,280:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    - Refresh Token (session continuity, device-bound)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,281:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4. App validates ID Token signature against GC IdP JWKS endpoint
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,282:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5. App checks acr claim meets minimum assurance level
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6. App checks amr claim includes required authentication methods
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 7. App stores tokens in HSM-backed storage
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 8. Subsequent API calls include DPoP-bound access token
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4 Why MFA Alone Is Insufficient
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) is a 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: necessary but not sufficient
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  control for GC mobile applications. Here is
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: why:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What MFA Protects Against:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ✅ Credential theft (password alone is not enough)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ✅ Remote account takeover from unknown devices
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,297:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ✅ Phishing attacks (partially — phishing-resistant MFA like FIDO2 is better)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What MFA Does NOT Protect Against:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Threat | Why MFA Fails |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|--------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stolen device with active session
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | MFA was already completed. If
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the session is alive, the attacker has full access. No re-authentication is triggered. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Token extraction from
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compromised device
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Bearer tokens stored in software-only storage can be exfiltrated. MFA doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t protect the
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: token at rest. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Man-in-the-middle on device
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Malware running on a rooted/jailbroken device can intercept tokens
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: post-MFA. MFA protects the authentication ceremony, not the post-auth session. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Session replay
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | A captured
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bearer token can be replayed from a different device. MFA verified the user, not the device presenting the token. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,327:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,328:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Push fatigue / MFA bombing
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,337:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Attackers repeatedly trigger push notifications until the user approves. This is a
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: known attack against push-based MFA. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,339:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SIM-swap for SMS OTP
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | SMS-based MFA is vulnerable to
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: carrier-level SIM swap attacks. Not appropriate for high-assurance scenarios. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Real-time phishing proxies
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Tools
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,354:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: like Evilginx2 can proxy the MFA ceremony in real-time, capturing both credentials and MFA tokens. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What Additional Controls Are Required:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Control | Purpose |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---------|---------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Device-bound tokens (DPoP)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,359:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Tokens are cryptographically bound to the
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,360:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: device
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s hardware key. Stolen tokens cannot be used elsewhere. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,365:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: App attestation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Verifies that the binary making
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the request is the genuine, unmodified GC application (not a repackaged or instrumented version). |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,372:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Device
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: integrity checks
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Detects rooted/jailbroken devices, active debuggers, or Frida/Xposed hooks. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Certificate-based
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: device identity
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,383:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Mutual TLS (mTLS) with a device certificate stored in the HSM creates a cryptographic device
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: identity independent of the user identity. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Continuous access evaluation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Server-side evaluation of device
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,394:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: compliance signals (MDM-reported) during token validation, not just at authentication time. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,395:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,396:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,398:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step-up
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: authentication
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | High-risk operations (e.g., data export, admin actions) trigger additional authentication even within
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: an active session. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Security Model:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MFA alone:           User Identity ✓  +  Device Identity ✗
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MFA + DPoP:          User Identity ✓  +  Device Identity ✓
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (token-bound)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MFA + DPoP + mTLS:   User Identity ✓  +  Device Identity ✓
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,421:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (channel-bound)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MFA + DPoP + Attest: User Identity ✓  +  Device Identity ✓ + App
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Integrity ✓
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,424:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The goal is 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: User + Device + App
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  verification at multiple layers.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.5 Device + Identity Coupling — Hardware-Backed Security
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: iOS — Secure Enclave
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The Secure Enclave is a dedicated hardware security coprocessor on Apple devices:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Key Generation:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,431:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Generates ECDSA P-256 key pairs that 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,432:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: never leave
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  the Secure Enclave. The
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: private key is not accessible to the application or the operating system.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,439:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Key Usage:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The app requests the Secure Enclave to sign a challenge/nonce; only the signature is
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: returned.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Biometric Gating:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,449:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Key usage can be gated by Face ID / Touch ID — the key is only usable with
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: biometric confirmation.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Access Control:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SecAccessControlCreateWithFlags
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  allows policies like 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .biometryCurrentSet
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (invalidated if biometrics change) and 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .privateKeyUsage
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,457:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: // Example: Creating a Secure Enclave-bound key for DPoP
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: let access = SecAccessControlCreateWithFlags(
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,458:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     kCFAllocatorDefault,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     kSecAttrAccessibleWhenUnlockedThisDeviceOnly,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     [.privateKeyUsage, .biometryCurrentSet],
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     nil
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )!
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: let attributes: [String: Any] = [
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     kSecAttrKeyType as String: kSecAttrKeyTypeECSECPrimeRandom,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     kSecAttrKeySizeInBits as String: 256,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     kSecAttrTokenID as String: kSecAttrTokenIDSecureEnclave,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     kSecPrivateKeyAttrs as String: [
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         kSecAttrIsPermanent as String: true,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         kSecAttrApplicationTag as String: "ca.gc.app.dpop-key",
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,469:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:         kSecAttrAccessControl as String: access
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,470:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     ]
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,471:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ]
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,472:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: var error: Unmanaged<CFError>?
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: let privateKey = SecKeyCreateRandomKey(attributes as CFDictionary,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,473:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &error)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,474:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Android — Keystore with StrongBox
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,475:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hardware-Backed Keystore:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  On devices with a dedicated HSM (StrongBox Keymaster), keys are
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: generated and stored in tamper-resistant hardware.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,482:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Key Attestation:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,486:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Android provides a certificate chain that cryptographically proves a key was
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: generated inside hardware. The GC backend can verify this chain.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,487:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Biometric Binding:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,488:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: setUserAuthenticationRequired(true)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  gates key usage on
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: biometric or device credential authentication.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: // Example: Creating a hardware-backed key for DPoP
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,494:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: val keyGenSpec = KeyGenParameterSpec.Builder(
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     "ca.gc.app.dpop-key",
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     KeyProperties.PURPOSE_SIGN or KeyProperties.PURPOSE_VERIFY
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,500:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     .setAlgorithmParameterSpec(ECGenParameterSpec("secp256r1"))
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,501:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     .setDigests(KeyProperties.DIGEST_SHA256)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     .setIsStrongBoxBacked(true)  // Require dedicated HSM
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     .setUserAuthenticationRequired(true)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,503:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     .setUserAuthenticationParameters(0,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: KeyProperties.AUTH_BIOMETRIC_STRONG)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,505:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     .setAttestationChallenge(serverNonce)  // Enable key
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: attestation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     .build()
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,508:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: val keyPairGenerator = KeyPairGenerator.getInstance(
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,509:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:     KeyProperties.KEY_ALGORITHM_EC, "AndroidKeyStore"
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: keyPairGenerator.initialize(keyGenSpec)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,511:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: val keyPair = keyPairGenerator.generateKeyPair()
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,516:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: React Native — Bridge-Dependent
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,517:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: React Native 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: does not
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  have direct access to Secure Enclave or Android Keystore from JavaScript. Access requires:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,520:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: native module
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  written in Swift/Kotlin that wraps the platform-specific HSM APIs
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The JavaScript layer calls the native module across the bridge
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,522:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The bridge serialization is a point of interception on compromised devices
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Libraries like 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,524:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: react-native-keychain
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,525:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: react-native-biometrics
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  provide partial abstraction, but:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,527:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: They may not support all Secure Enclave features (e.g., key attestation)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,531:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Custom native modules are often required for full DPoP and mTLS implementations
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,532:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The bridge introduces latency for performance-sensitive cryptographic operations
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.6 Client Certificate Verification with HSM
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Client certificate (mTLS) authentication provides a 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,534:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transport-layer device identity
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,535:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  that complements the
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: application-layer OAuth/OIDC identity:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                    mTLS Handshake                              │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,541:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                                                               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  1. Client initiates TLS connection to GC API gateway          │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  2. Server presents its certificate (standard TLS)             │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,547:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  3. Server requests client certificate (CertificateRequest)    │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  4. Client retrieves certificate chain from device store       │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  5. Client signs the TLS handshake with HSM-stored private key │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,549:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  6. Server validates:                                          │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,550:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     a. Certificate chain → GC-trusted CA                       │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     b. Certificate not revoked (CRL/OCSP)                      │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,552:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     c. Certificate subject matches expected device identity    │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  7. TLS session established with mutual authentication         │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                                                               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  Result: Every byte transmitted is bound to a verified device  │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,555:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Device Certificate Lifecycle:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Phase | Process |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,557:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-------|---------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,558:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Provisioning
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | During MDM enrollment, a device certificate is generated with the
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,571:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: private key in the HSM. The CSR (Certificate Signing Request) is sent to the GC PKI CA. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,574:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Storage
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,579:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Private key
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: resides exclusively in Secure Enclave (iOS) or StrongBox Keystore (Android). It cannot be exported. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,581:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,583:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Rotation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,588:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Certificates have a defined validity period (e.g., 1 year). Automated renewal via MDM or SCEP/EST protocol. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,590:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Revocation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,592:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | MDM can trigger revocation on device wipe, policy violation, or compromise detection. OCSP
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,594:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stapling provides real-time revocation checking. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,596:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Combined Flow — mTLS + OAuth 2.1 + DPoP:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Layer 1 (TLS):     Device ←──mTLS──→ API Gateway     → Device is
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,598:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: authenticated
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Layer 2 (OAuth):   User   ←──DPoP token──→ Resource    → User is
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,601:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: authorized  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,602:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Layer 3 (App):     Binary ←──Attestation──→ Verifier   → App is genuine
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,604:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Three independent verification layers. Compromise of one does not
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,605:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: break the others.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,608:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.7 Reducing Login Prompts — Silent Token Renewal
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,609:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A core usability requirement is minimizing login friction while maintaining security. The following strategies
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,611:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: achieve this:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,612:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Strategy 1: Long-Lived Refresh Tokens with Short-Lived Access Tokens
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,613:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,614:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Access tokens: 5–15 minute lifetime (limits damage if intercepted)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,616:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Refresh tokens: 24–48 hours (enables silent renewal without user interaction)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,617:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The SDK silently exchanges the refresh token for a new access token before expiry
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: User only sees a login prompt when the refresh token expires
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,619:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Strategy 2: Biometric-Gated Token Access
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tokens stored with 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,621:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: biometryCurrentSet
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  access control
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: First use after device unlock triggers a biometric prompt (invisible or quick)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,623:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Subsequent uses within the authentication window do not prompt
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This replaces repeated password entry with a single passive biometric confirmation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Strategy 3: Background Token Refresh
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,630:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The app proactively refreshes tokens in the background before they expire
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Push notifications from the backend can trigger a refresh cycle
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,635:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The user never encounters an expired token during active use
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,637:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Strategy 4: Session Continuity with Device Trust
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,638:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,640:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If the device passes integrity attestation and the refresh token is valid, the session continues
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Re-authentication is only required when:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,642:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,643:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Refresh token expires
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Device trust state changes (e.g., jailbreak detected, MDM compliance lost)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,645:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A sensitive operation triggers step-up authentication
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,647:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Maximum session lifetime is reached (policy-driven, e.g., 8 hours)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,648:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.8 Authentication Possibilities — Complete Landscape
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,649:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Method | Description | Assurance Level | Pros | Cons | GC Applicability |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,650:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|-------------|----------------|------|------|-----------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,651:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,652:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OIDC + PKCE
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,661:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Standard browser-based OIDC flow
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,665:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: with PKCE | Moderate | Well-understood, standard, broad library support | User leaves app for system browser auth |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,666:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ✅ Baseline for all apps |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,667:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,668:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OIDC + PKCE + DPoP
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,673:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | OIDC with proof-of-possession tokens | High | Token theft is
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mitigated; device-bound | Requires HSM integration; more complex | ✅ Recommended for sensitive apps |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,675:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,676:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,679:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OIDC +
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,680:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PKCE + DPoP + mTLS
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,686:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Full mutual TLS plus token binding | Very High | Three-layer verification; payload
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,688:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: encrypted end-to-end | Certificate management overhead; MDM dependency | ✅ Required for Protected B |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,689:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,690:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: FIDO2 /
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,691:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WebAuthn (Passkeys)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,704:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Passwordless hardware-key authentication | Very High | Phishing-resistant; no shared
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: secrets; hardware-backed | GC IdP must support FIDO2; passkey provisioning needed | ⚠️ Emerging — pilot
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: recommended |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,709:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Certificate-Based Authentication (CBA)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,721:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | User authenticates with a personal smart card / derived
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: credential | Very High | Strong assurance; aligned with existing GC PKI | Requires smart card infrastructure; poor
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,729:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mobile UX | ⚠️ Limited — for high-assurance roles |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,731:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,733:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SMS OTP (MFA factor)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | One-time code via SMS | Low | Simple;
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: widely available | SIM-swap vulnerable; real-time phishing; NIST discourages for high assurance | ❌ Discouraged |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Push-based MFA
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Approve/deny notification on a registered device | Moderate | Better UX than OTP; harder to
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: phish than SMS | Push fatigue attacks; requires separate registered device | ⚠️ Acceptable as one factor |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TOTP
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Authenticator App)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Time-based one-time password | Moderate | Offline-capable; no carrier dependency | Shared
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: secret can be extracted from authenticator backup; phishable in real-time | ⚠️ Acceptable as one factor |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Biometric
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Local)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,783:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Face ID / Touch ID to gate local key access | Complementary | Fast, intuitive, non-transferable | Not a
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,784:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remote authentication method; only gates local key usage | ✅ Combine with token storage |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5. WebView Shell vs. Locally-Hosted Application — Security Analysis
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This section provides a detailed comparison between two architectures:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Architecture A — WebView Shell:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A native app containing a full-screen 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WKWebView
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  / 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WebView
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,790:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  that loads a
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remotely hosted web application (e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,791:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: https://app.service.canada.ca
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ).
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Architecture B — Local React Native App:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  A React Native application where all HTML, JavaScript, and application
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: logic is bundled into the binary and runs locally on the device.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Security Dimension | WebView Shell (Remote) | React Native (Local) | Risk Delta |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-------------------|----------------------|---------------------|------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Code Origin
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Downloaded at runtime from
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remote server | Bundled at build time, signed and distributed via app stores | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Critical
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — Remote code cannot be verified
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: at runtime |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Code Integrity
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | No guarantee — CDN compromise or MITM injects code | App store code signing +
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: binary integrity verification | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Critical
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Token Storage
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: localStorage
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  / cookies — software-only, extractable |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Keychain / Keystore via native modules — hardware-backed | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Critical
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,822:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: XSS Vulnerability
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,828:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Full exposure — any
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reflected/stored XSS in the web app compromises the WebView session | No DOM-based web context; React
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Native renders native views | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: High
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: JavaScript Injection
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: evaluateJavaScript()
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  can inject arbitrary code
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: into the WebView | JS bundle is static; no runtime injection vector (if CodePush is disabled) | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: High
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Network
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Dependency
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | App is non-functional offline; degraded service on poor networks | Full offline capability for cached
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data and UI; API calls for new data | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Medium
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Certificate Pinning
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Extremely difficult in WebView — system TLS
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stack is used | Achievable via native modules (
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: react-native-ssl-pinning
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ) | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: High
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Deep Linking / URL
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Schemes
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | WebView URL handling can be manipulated to navigate to malicious sites | React Native navigation is
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: internal; external URLs require explicit handling | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Medium
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cookie Security
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | WebView cookies are shared with
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: the system cookie jar; accessible to debuggers | No cookie layer; tokens managed in native encrypted storage | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,899:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: High
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,900:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,901:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,902:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Content Security Policy
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | CSP headers help but are bypassable if attacker controls the response | Not applicable —
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: no web content to protect | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Low
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,906:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Device API Access
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Limited to what 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WKWebView
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  / 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WebView
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  exposes via
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bridge | Full native API access via native modules | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Medium
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Debugging / Inspection
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Safari/Chrome DevTools
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can inspect WebView content in debug builds; some access on rooted devices in production | React Native Hermes
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,945:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bytecode is harder to debug; native modules are compiled | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,947:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Medium
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,948:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,949:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,950:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,951:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Regulatory Compliance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,955:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Difficult to
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,956:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: demonstrate code integrity for security assessments | Build artifacts are auditable; SBOM generation is standard | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,957:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: High
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,958:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Verdict
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,960:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For applications that handle personal information, Protected A, or Protected B data, organizations should carefully
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,962:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: consider the following:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,964:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: WebView shell applications present significant challenges in meeting typical enterprise
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,965:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: security requirements.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,971:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The limitations around code integrity, hardware-backed token storage, and
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,973:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: injection resistance make this architecture a higher-risk choice that may not satisfy security
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,974:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: assessment criteria.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Organizations choosing this pattern should do so with an 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,975:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: informed risk acceptance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,983:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  and documented rationale. A
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,985:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: locally-bundled React Native application or a fully native application generally provides a stronger security posture.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,986:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6. Cross-Cutting Concerns
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,988:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.1 Logging
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,990:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Logging in a mobile context differs fundamentally from server-side logging. Logs reside on a user
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,991:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,992:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s device and must
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,993:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: be treated with extreme sensitivity.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,995:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Aspect | Guidance |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,996:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|----------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,997:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:30,998:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What to Log
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,002:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | App lifecycle events, authentication success/failure, API call
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,003:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: results (status codes only), navigation events, crash data, performance metrics. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,004:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: What NOT to Log
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,008:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Tokens,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: credentials, PII, request/response bodies, user input, biometric data, device identifiers that could enable tracking. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,009:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,011:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,012:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Storage
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,015:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Logs should be encrypted at rest. Use OS-provided encrypted storage. Implement log rotation with
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: maximum retention (e.g., 7 days on-device). |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,016:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,017:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Exfiltration Protection
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,018:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Logs should not be extractable from the
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: device without the app
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,019:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s cooperation. On non-managed devices, logs should be encrypted with an app-specific key. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,020:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,021:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Remote Collection
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,028:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | For centralized observability, logs should be transmitted to the backend over mTLS channels.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,031:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Collection should comply with applicable privacy requirements. User consent may be required. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,032:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,033:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Structured
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,034:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Format
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Use structured logging (JSON) with consistent fields: timestamp (ISO 8601), correlation ID, severity,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,036:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: component, event type. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Platform Comparison:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,037:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Feature | Native iOS | Native Android | React Native |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,038:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---------|-----------|---------------|--------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,039:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | OS-level
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,040:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: logging | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,041:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: os_log
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  with privacy annotations | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,042:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Log
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,043:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (filtered in release) | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,044:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: console.log
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,046:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (must be stripped) |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,047:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,048:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Crash
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reporting | MetricKit, native crash handlers | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,049:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Thread.UncaughtExceptionHandler
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Requires native crash
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,051:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: handler bridge |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,052:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Log encryption | Straightforward with CryptoKit | Straightforward with Jetpack Security | Requires
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,054:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: native module |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,055:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Privacy annotations | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: os_log
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,056:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  supports 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,057:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: %{private}
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Manual redaction required | Manual
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,058:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: redaction required |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,059:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.2 Auditing
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,062:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Auditing captures 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,064:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: who did what, when, and from where
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,065:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for accountability and compliance. Unlike logging, audit
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,066:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: records are 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: immutable, authoritative, and retained long-term
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,067:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,068:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Requirement | Implementation |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,069:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-------------|---------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,070:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,071:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Audit Events
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,073:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Login, logout, data access, data
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,074:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: modification, permission changes, export operations, attestation results. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,075:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,076:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Audit Fields
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,084:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | User ID (sub claim),
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,086:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: device ID, timestamp, action, resource, outcome, session ID, IP address (captured server-side). |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,088:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,089:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,090:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Client-Side Role
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,099:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,102:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The mobile app generates audit event payloads and transmits them to the backend audit service. The app is NOT the
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: system of record. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,103:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,104:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Tamper Resistance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,105:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Audit events should be signed with the device
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,109:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s HSM-bound key before
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: transmission. The backend verifies the signature against the registered device public key. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Offline Audit
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,116:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Events
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,118:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: generated offline should be queued in encrypted storage and transmitted when connectivity is restored, with original
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: timestamps preserved. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,120:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Retention
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,122:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Audit records retained per GC MITS and departmental retention schedules
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (typically 2–7 years). |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.3 Distributed Tracing
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,126:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Distributed tracing correlates a single user operation across the mobile app, API gateway, backend microservices,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,127:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: and data stores.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Aspect | Implementation |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,128:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|---------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Standard
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | W3C Trace Context (
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: traceparent
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,133:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  / 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: tracestate
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,134:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: headers) |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,135:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Trace Initiation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | The mobile app generates a trace ID at the start of each user operation and propagates
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: it through all API calls. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,140:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,141:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,142:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Span Structure
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Mobile app creates spans for: UI interaction → API call → response
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: processing. Backend continues the trace. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,151:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Correlation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Every API request includes 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,152:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: traceparent
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  header.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Backend logs and traces share the same trace ID. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Sensitive Data
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Spans should NOT include PII, tokens, or
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: request/response bodies. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,160:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,164:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SDK Options
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | OpenTelemetry SDKs exist for iOS (swift), Android (kotlin), and
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: JavaScript (React Native). |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,167:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Platform Comparison:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Feature | Native iOS | Native Android | React Native |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,170:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---------|-----------|---------------|--------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,172:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | OTEL SDK
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: maturity | Stable | Stable | Stable (JS SDK) |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,174:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Automatic instrumentation | Network (URLSession) | Network
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,177:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (OkHttp) | Fetch/XMLHttpRequest |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | UI interaction tracing | Manual spans required | Manual spans required |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Manual spans required |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Performance overhead | Low | Low | Low-Medium (bridge calls) |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.4 Authorization
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Authorization determines 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: what an authenticated user is allowed to do
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . This is distinct from authentication (which
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,204:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: establishes identity).
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,205:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Pattern | Description | Pros | Cons |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---------|-------------|------|------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,207:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,208:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Token-embedded claims
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Roles/permissions
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: encoded in the access token (JWT claims) | Fast — no network call for authorization decisions; offline-capable | Token
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: bloat; stale permissions until token refresh; limited complexity |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Remote policy evaluation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,233:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Each operation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: queries a Policy Decision Point (PDP) like OPA or Cedar | Fine-grained, real-time, centralized policy management |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,239:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Network dependency; latency on every decision; single point of failure |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,241:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hybrid
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,245:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Token claims for broad role
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: checks; remote PDP for sensitive operations | Balanced performance and granularity | More complex
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,247:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: implementation |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,248:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Recommendations for GC Mobile:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Use 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: token claims
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,251:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for basic role-based access (e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,252:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: is this user an inspector?
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,253:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,254:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Use 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: remote policy evaluation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,255:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  for sensitive operations (e.g., 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,256:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: can this user export this file from this
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,257:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: device at this location?
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,258:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: )
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,259:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Cache policy decisions locally with a 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,260:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: short TTL
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,261:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (e.g., 5 minutes) for offline resilience
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,262:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Implement 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: RBAC at minimum
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,263:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ; consider 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,264:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ABAC
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,265:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Attribute-Based Access Control) for complex
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: multi-departmental scenarios
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,266:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.5 Error Handling and Resilience
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Concern | Practice |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,267:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---------|----------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,268:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,269:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,270:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Error Classification
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,272:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Differentiate between recoverable (network timeout),
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: user-actionable (auth expired), and fatal (data corruption) errors. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,274:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,275:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: User-Facing Messages
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,283:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Never expose stack
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,285:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: traces, server error details, or technical identifiers to the user. Use generic, bilingual error messages with error codes
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,286:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for support reference. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Retry Strategy
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Implement exponential backoff with jitter for transient failures. Circuit
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: breaker pattern for persistent failures. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,293:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Offline Mode
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Define explicit offline capabilities. Queue mutations for
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,299:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: sync. Clearly indicate stale data to the user. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,300:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Crash Recovery
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,307:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Persist application state periodically. On restart
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: after crash, restore to last known good state. Never resume a session that may have been compromised by the crash. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.6 Performance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,310:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Metric | Target | Measurement |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:31,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|--------|-------------|
