   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,106:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Microsoft Sentinel + Logic Apps | ✅ Microsoft Sentinel + Logic Apps | ⚠️ Limited telemetry for triggers |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,108:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 9.2 Microsoft Technology Stack for SIE Response
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,110:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The following Microsoft services form the recommended SIE response stack for mobile applications:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Layer | Service | Role in SIE Response |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,111:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-------|---------|---------------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,112:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Identity
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,113:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,114:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Microsoft Entra ID
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,119:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Conditional Access, Continuous Access Evaluation) | Real-time session evaluation; revoke access based on risk
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,123:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: signals; enforce device compliance at token refresh |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,124:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Device Management
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,125:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,125:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Microsoft Intune
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,129:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Remote wipe
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (full/selective); compliance policy enforcement; certificate revocation; app data removal |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,130:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Threat Detection
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,131:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,132:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Microsoft Defender for Endpoint
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,136:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (Mobile Threat Defense) | On-device threat detection (jailbreak, network threats,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: malicious apps); risk level signals fed to Entra Conditional Access |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,137:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: SIEM/SOAR
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,138:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,139:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Microsoft Sentinel
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,143:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,147:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Centralized incident detection from mobile telemetry; automated playbooks via Logic Apps/SOAR; correlation with
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: broader organizational signals |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,148:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,149:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Observability
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,150:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Azure Monitor + Application Insights
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,153:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Real-time telemetry
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ingestion; anomaly detection on mobile API patterns; custom alerts for SIE indicators |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,154:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,155:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Communication
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,156:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Microsoft Teams
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,157:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (via Sentinel integration) | Automated SIE notification to incident response teams; escalation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,158:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: workflows |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 9.3 SIE Response Playbook — Recommended Pattern
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,159:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,162:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                SIE DETECTION → CONTAINMENT FLOW                  │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,163:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,166:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                                                                  │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,168:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  1. DETECT (seconds)                                             │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,169:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── Defender for Endpoint detects device compromise          │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,171:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── Sentinel correlates anomalous API patterns               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,173:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     └── Entra ID detects impossible travel / risky sign-in       │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,175:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                                                                  │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,176:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  2. SIGNAL (seconds)                                             │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,178:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── Risk signal propagated to Entra Conditional Access       │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,179:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── Device compliance state updated in Intune                │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,180:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     └── Sentinel incident created automatically                  │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,181:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                                                                  │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,182:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  3. CONTAIN (seconds to minutes)                                 │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,183:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── Conditional Access blocks token refresh (CAE)            │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── Intune triggers selective wipe of app data               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,184:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── DPoP-bound tokens become invalid (key revoked)           │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,185:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     └── mTLS certificate revoked via OCSP                        │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,186:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                                                                  │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,187:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  4. NOTIFY (minutes)                                             │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,188:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── Sentinel playbook notifies SOC via Teams                 │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,189:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── Automated incident ticket created                        │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,190:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     └── Affected user notified via push / email                  │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                                                                  │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,191:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  5. REMEDIATE (minutes to hours)                                 │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,192:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── Device re-enrollment required (Intune)                   │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,194:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── New device certificate provisioned                       │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,197:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     ├── User re-authenticates with step-up MFA                   │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,199:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │     └── Forensic audit trail preserved in Sentinel               │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,200:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │                                                                  │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,201:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  Total time from detection to containment: < 5 minutes           │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  (with Continuous Access Evaluation and automated playbooks)     │
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,203:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,206:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 9.4 Continuous Access Evaluation (CAE) — Critical SIE Enabler
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,210:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Microsoft Entra ID Continuous Access Evaluation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,213:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is a key differentiator for SIE response. Unlike traditional
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,214:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: token-based sessions that remain valid until expiry:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,215:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CAE enables 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,216:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: near-real-time
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,217:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  revocation of access tokens when critical events occur (user disabled,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: password changed, high-risk detection)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,218:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Resource servers subscribe to 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,219:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: critical event notifications
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  from Entra ID
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,220:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Token lifetime is effectively reduced to 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,221:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: minutes
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  rather than the standard expiry window
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,222:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Combined with DPoP, a compromised token is both 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,223:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: revocable
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (CAE) and 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,224:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: non-transferable
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,225:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (hardware-bound)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,226:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Architecture implication:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,240:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Native and React Native (with native modules) applications can fully
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,244:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leverage CAE through the Microsoft Authentication Library (MSAL). WebView shell applications
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,246:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: have limited CAE integration capabilities.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,249:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 10. Recommendations and Next Steps
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,250:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Note:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,273:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  The following recommendations are advisory in nature. Each organization should evaluate
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,284:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: these against their specific regulatory environment, risk tolerance, operational capacity, and existing
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,287:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: infrastructure before adoption. Microsoft provides this guidance to inform decision-making, not to
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,288:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: prescribe a specific course of action.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,289:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Suggested Actions for Consideration
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,290:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Establish a Mobile Security Baseline
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,291:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Consider defining minimum security requirements per data classification
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,292:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,294:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Evaluate OIDC + PKCE + DPoP as a baseline for new mobile applications
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,295:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,296:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Assess whether WebView shell architecture meets your organization
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,298:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,301:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s security
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: requirements for applications handling sensitive data
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,303:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,305:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Evaluate hardware-backed key storage on all supported devices
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,306:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,308:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Consider a Shared Security Module Library
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,309:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,311:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Whether choosing native or React Native, evaluate building (or procuring) a shared
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,312:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: library of security primitives:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,313:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: HSM key generation and signing
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,314:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DPoP proof generation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,315:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mTLS client certificate handling
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,316:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,317:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Device attestation (App Attest / Play Integrity)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,318:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Jailbreak/root detection
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,319:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,320:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A centrally maintained library can reduce duplication and improve consistency
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,321:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: across mobile projects
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,322:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Develop a Mobile Threat Model Template
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,323:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Based on OWASP MASTG and STRIDE, consider creating an organization-specific
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,325:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: threat model template
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,326:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,330:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Include organization-specific threats: cross-border device usage, official languages
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,331:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: requirements, enterprise IdP integration
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,332:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Evaluate FIDO2 / Passkeys
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,333:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,335:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Engage with the enterprise IdP team to evaluate FIDO2 / Passkey support
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,336:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,338:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This represents a significant potential usability + security improvement
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,342:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,344:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Eliminates passwords entirely; hardware-bound; phishing-resistant
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,346:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Architecture Principles
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | # | Principle | Rationale |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,347:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |---|-----------|-----------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,348:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 1 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,349:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Assume the device is compromised
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,353:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Design all security
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: controls to be resilient to a rooted/jailbroken device. Defense-in-depth, not perimeter-only. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,355:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,356:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 2 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Never trust the
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,357:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: client
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,358:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | All authorization decisions should be validated server-side. Client-side checks are for UX only. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,359:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,359:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 3 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,361:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hardware-bind all secrets
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,363:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Every cryptographic key and credential should be stored in the platform
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,364:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,367:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s hardware
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,368:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: security module where available. Software-only key storage introduces additional risk. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,369:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 4 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,370:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Minimize on-device
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,371:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: data
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Store the minimum data required for functionality. Treat the device as a transient view into backend data, not
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,373:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a data store. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,374:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 5 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,375:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Log everything, expose nothing
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Comprehensive observability with strict PII/credential
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,376:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: redaction. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,377:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 6 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,378:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Build for both languages from day one
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,384:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Retrofitting localization is expensive. String
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,385:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: externalization and flexible layout should be in the initial architecture. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,386:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 7 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,387:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Test security continuously
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,389:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Automated
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,390:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: security testing (SAST, DAST, dependency scanning) in CI/CD. Periodic OWASP MASTG assessments. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,391:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 8 | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Plan
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,392:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for offline
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,397:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Even if offline is not a V1 requirement, the data layer should support it. Retrofitting offline sync is
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,399:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: architecturally disruptive. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,401:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 11. Appendix — Glossary and References
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,402:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Glossary
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Term | Definition |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,403:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|-----------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,404:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,405:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CAE
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,408:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Continuous Access Evaluation — Microsoft Entra ID capability for
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,409:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: near-real-time token revocation based on critical security events. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,411:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,412:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,413:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: DPoP
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,415:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Demonstrating Proof-of-Possession — RFC
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,416:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 9449. Mechanism to bind access tokens to a client
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,417:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s public key. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,418:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,419:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: HSM
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Hardware Security Module — dedicated
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: hardware for cryptographic operations and key storage. On mobile: Secure Enclave (iOS), StrongBox/TEE
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: (Android). |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,426:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,427:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: mTLS
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,428:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Mutual TLS — both client and server present certificates during the TLS handshake. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,429:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,430:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PKCE
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,434:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,435:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Proof Key for Code Exchange — RFC 7636. Mitigates authorization code interception in public clients. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,436:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,437:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,438:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OIDC
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,441:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,442:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: OpenID Connect — identity layer built on OAuth 2.0/2.1. Provides ID tokens and standard claims. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,443:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,444:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,446:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GC IdP
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,453:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Government of Canada Identity Provider — the enterprise identity service for federal authentication. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,455:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MSAL
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,459:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,460:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Microsoft Authentication Library — SDK for integrating with Microsoft Entra ID across platforms. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,461:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,462:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,463:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: MASTG
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  | Mobile
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,465:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Application Security Testing Guide — OWASP
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,466:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,467:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s comprehensive mobile security testing methodology. |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-13 14:51:32,468:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 
